  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CFD hemolysis credibility assessment (CPB)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning-augmented CFD hemolysis prediction pipeline applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. A gradient-boosted neural network surrogate (three hidden layers, ReLU activation) was trained on 4,200 CFD-derived shear-stress trajectories to predict the relative hemolysis index (RH) across 5 flow-speed operating points. The surrogate accelerates design-space exploration; CFD validation cases anchor the physical fidelity. COU1 evaluates whether the combined model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment completed.",
